FBIS3-52145 "drnes001_p_94005" FBIS-NES-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Fighting Between Rabbani, Dostam Forces Dostam Forces Tighten Siege on Kabul LD0301112394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1030 GMT 3 Jan 94 LD0301112394 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Text] Sources close to Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of Afghanistan] say that troops of the forces opposed to President Borhanoddin Rabbani of Afghanistan are tightening their siege on Kabul and on the forces loyal to Hezb-e Jam'iat-e Eslami [Islamic Society of Afghanistan] from the east, south, and north of the city. Forces affiliated to Ahmed Shah Mas'ud have reported the arrest of 300 troops loyal to General Dostam. The Afghan Embassy in Islamabad announced that heavy clashes have occurred between forces of Rabbani and General Dostam in Faryab and Sheberghan. Meanwhile Hezb-e Wahhdat-e Eslami [Islamic Unity Party of Afghanistan] announced that the experience of the war during the past 20 months has demonstrated that none of the warring sides will gain victory and that Hezb-e Wahhdat-e Eslami will not side with any of the warring factions, but will endeavor to terminate the war in which the people are suffering the most.
